Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the @macaroni{180%g}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g}(grated).

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @breadcrumbs{25%g}, @mixed herbs{1%sachet} and the @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the crumb. Set the crumb aside.

When your pan of water is boiling, stir in the macaroni and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Melt in the @butter{20%g}.

Once the oil is hot, add the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%min}, then stir in the @plain flour{1.5%tbsp} and cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%mins} - you've made a roux!

Stir in the @water{200%ml} a little at a time, followed by the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @vegetable stock paste{15%g}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer, stirring until thickened, ~{2-3%mins}.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Once the sauce has thickened, remove from the heat, then stir through the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}, Cheddar, @fresh pesto{32%g}, @peas{120%g} and cooked macaroni.

Add a splash of water if it's a little thick. Taste and season with salt and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

Transfer the creamy pasta to an #ovenproof dish{} and top evenly with the herby crumb.

Place your mac and cheese on a #baking tray{} and grill until golden, ~{4-5%mins}.

Share your pesto mac and cheese between your plates. Enjoy!